  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed roof extension would be an overly dominant and unsympathetic addition to the property. Furthermore, the building up of the rear butterfly parapet would constitute an inappropriate and harmful form of development. The proposal would, therefore, be harmful to the character and appearance of the host building, the terrace to which it belongs, and the wider East Canonbury Conservation Area. The proposal is therefore contrary to Policies D1, D4, D11, D22, D25, and D42 of Islington's Unitary Development Plan (2002), Islington's Conservation Area Design Guideline (2002), and Islington's Urban Design Guide (2006)."
